OL,3,CVictim of Laos alcohol poisoning warns
OL,4,Cholidaymakers of dangers
OL,6,F"We're not teaching children about
OL,7,Fthis at schools, and I think the
OL,8,Ftravel industry could do a lot more."
OL,10,FThere are official counterfeit alcohol
OL,11,Fwarnings for travellers to the
OL,12,Ffollowing countries:
OL,14,FThe Foreign Office warns that symptoms
OL,15,Fmay take up to 48 hours to appear. It
OL,16,Fsays: "If you're feeling very drunk,
OL,17,Fout of proportion to how much you've
OL,18,Fhad, get help".
